<title type="html"><![CDATA[Offering The Sunnah Salaah At Home]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1078&amp;p=1138#p1138"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">Offering The Sunnah Salaah At Home</span></strong><br /><br /><em>The Fourteenth question of Fatwa no. 6259</em><br /><br /><span style="color: #0000FF">Q14: Is it better to offer the Sunnah Salah (supererogatory prayers) and the Nawafil (extra supererogatory prayers) such as the Shaf' (two units of Prayer, particularly before the final unit of the odd-number prayer), and the Witr (Prayer with an odd-number of units) at home or in the Masjid (Mosque)?</span><br /><br />A: It is mentioned in Sahih Muslim, in a long Hadith that the Prophet (Peace &amp; Blessings of Allah be upon him) said: <br /><br />&quot;You should perform (optional) prayers in your houses, for the best prayer performed by a person that offered in one's house, except the obligatory.&quot;<br /><br />There is also the Hadith, &quot;The best prayer of a person is what which they pray in their house except the obligatory prayers.&quot;<br /><br /><em>Permenent Committee for Scholarly Research and Ifta'</em><br /><br />Member - Abdullah ibn Qa'ud<br />Member - Abdullah ibn Ghudayyan<br />Deputy Chairman - Abdul-Razzaq Afify<br />Chariman - Abdul Aziz bin Baz<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> â€” Fri Feb 03, 2017 11:56 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
